144816326.review:
Pros:
[list]
[*]Those 3 minutes of managing the cabaret club, optimizing profits while thinking of the girls' moods and growth;
[*][b]Majima[/b]'s side of the game. His personality, fighting styles, some substories, and parts of the main story;
[*]Combat is fine, overall.
[/list]

Cons:
[list]
[*][b]The writing[/b]. The story has twists akin to latin-american telenovelas, and all except two are completely predictable. You know the twist from Chapter 10 is coming since Chapter 2. None of the twists are smart, I deeply regret wasting time watching the story unfold;
[*][b]Too many prompts[/b] and unskippable animations/cutscenes. As an example, getting into an arcade machine costs you 20 seconds and 5 clicks instead of 2 seconds and 1 click. This permeates every aspect of the game and is especially a problem mostly because of the next two cons;
[*][b]Excessive amount of minigames[/b] that are, at best, just passable. Most are boring, some are overly complicated, others are both. You're better off playing some other game instead of trying to learn mahjong or pocket car customization;
[*][b]Not enough animations[/b], songs, and soundbites in the substories. There are 100 of them, but I feel like there are only 8 animations the NPCs do as to not just be barfing text and soundbites while standing still, and only 4 songs to add mood to what's happening. That's not nearly enough to not make them irritatingly repetitive.
